==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Millefiore glass
<hw>Mil`le*fi*o"re glass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It. <ets>mille</ets>
thousand + <ets>fiore</ets> flower.]</ety> <def>Slender rods or tubes of
colored glass fused together and embedded in clear glass; -- used for
paperweights and other small articles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Millenarian</ent>⟦br⟧
